Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper deals with unsupervised word mapping between languages, which falls under the domain of natural language processing (NLP) and language modeling. 
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper uses visual grounding to establish a common visual representation between two languages, which involves computer vision techniques such as image and video processing. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a hybrid visual-text mapping algorithm, which involves machine learning techniques such as deep learning and embedding learning. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper's approach of using visual grounding to improve unsupervised word mapping can be seen as an application of artificial intelligence to language translation. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with instructional videos as a source of data for learning embeddings, which falls under the domain of multimedia processing and analysis.
